<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - WEST COAST MAGNUM MIRRORS AND AERO MIRRORS - WEST COAST
        MAGNUM SERVICE PROCEDURES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>WEST COAST MAGNUM SERVICE PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcproc id="x1602801" svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Mirror Head Replacement</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16028_3.xml" xrefid="f1602802">Figure 2</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use an appropriate tool to remove the strain relief from the lower end of the mirror
                    body. Pull wires out of mirror body as far as possible. Cut all wires at the mirror body exit point.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On the "C" loop wire harness strip back approximately 2" of insulation to expose all
                    wires in the bundle. Strip &#188;" from each wire. Mirror configuration will determine the number
                    and color of wires in the bundle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gray plastic thread caps from the upper and lower mirror pivot rod ends.
                    Remove the locknut and washer from the upper pivot rod.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the upper short diagonal brace.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the mirror head and remove the lower locknut and washer from the lower pivot
                    rod.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the mirror head out of the lower mounting bracket and brace.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
